	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">

		<table width="100%">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Magician guide to level 13</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:tim_gerber@yahoo.com">Zuranthium</a> | 
		            1/20/2000 2:50:16 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">  I just wanted to say I REALLY hate it when people are making all these stupid guides on how to get to level 5 and crap. You should be at least level 8 to submit a guide in because no one should need help getting to level 5...everything you need to get to that level should be in your newbie zone.  Anyway to the guide.<BR>
  I started out as a gnome. I like roleplaying short people so it was good race for me. Besides roleplaying qualities they have great int, above average agility and dex, and infravision. I think it is totally necessary to be a race with infravision if it is your first time playing. My first character was a barbarian shaman...and man did I get confused during the night. If you don't wanna be a gnome then i suggest being a high elf and going to aakanon when you start(or once you get to level 4).<BR>
  Anyway I started in aakanon, the nice gnome city.  There are robot guides throughout the city and if you talk to them they can led you to your guild or any shops.  You have to type in the exact right thing though so play around with it.<BR>
  Getting to level 4 should be very easy. Just always have minor shielding on and cast burst of fire to pull stuff in and then attack it. Kill anything that cons white or blue, at this level it will be very easy. Watch out for the spiders though they will gang up on you.  Hopefully you will get a cracked staff of the corpse of a decaying gnome. It is a very good weapon for the low levels. <BR>
  Once you get to level 4 i suggest getting these spells: elementalkin earth, burn, summon bandages, summon food, summon water, gate.  Once you get summon bandages you should start practing bind wound.  It will heal your hp up to 1/2 health and when you group people will enjoy it.<BR>
  Once you have all of your spells scribed and memorized go to the kobold camp that has level 4-5 kobolds. Summon your pet(after going to the gem shop and buying malachite, just ask someone to guide you there) and then con it.  If it cons white or yellow then keep it. If it cons blue type /pet get lost and summon another until you get a white or blue.  Now that you have a pet click on a kobold and type /pet attack. Your pet will go up and star attacking. Once your pet does this cast a few burn spells on the kobold. Frequently type /pet report health. Once your pet gets down to about 40% health go in and tank. Doing this you should easily be able to kill the kobolds. There is only one problem, there are three kobolds at the camp. So you will have to group with someone else thats level 4-5 to help you out. If there is another group there alreayd then just share the kobolds with them...they will keep the extra kobolds busy. Doing this you should easily be able to get to level 7. Once you get to level 7 some of the kobolds will start to con green. At this point if you have two options, stay at this camp and kill the kobolds without a pet, or go to the other kobold camp that has kobolds that are a level higher. If you stay at the camp(which is what i did) you will level very slowly. However you will also build up some preety good loot becuase even though you don't get exp. for killing green kobolds you can still loot them. If you go to the other kobold camp you will definately need another person or two to help you. There are 4 kobolds and this camp so it is definately out to go there alone. After fighting for a while at whichever camp you should get to level 8(and it takes a long time..trust me, level 7 is the hell level for casters).<BR>
  Once you get to level 8 you need to go buy your new spells. Gte these ones: elementaling earth, shock of blades, flame shield, invisibility, lesser shielding, and staff of tracing(i didn't get the staff of tracing though...magicians are not a melee class so i didn't care about weaponry).  You will probably find that you don't have enough money to buy all these spells.  Thats all right just ask a higher level player(yes i know this is short of cheating). Higher level players will give you a few plat and after asking enough of them you should have all your spells. Now once you get to level 8 and have all your awesome spells go to lesser faydark tot he orc hill(again ask someone to take you). You will need to group with 3-4 other people for this place so ask around. The easiest way is to type /who all 8-10. This will tell you everyone that is levels 8-10 in the game. Ask all the people that are levels 8-10 to come join you until you have a party of 5 or 6 people(although make sure they are close to you...zones which are close enough to lesser faydark for them to come are butcherblock, greater faydark, crush bone, steamfount, and akkanon). Just kill these orcs in a group until you hit level 12(although as you go up in levels you won't need quite as many people to group with you). When fighting be sure to keep the tanks of the group buffed up with your flame shield spell, it does a lot of damage over time even if it does take a good amount of mana.<BR>
  Once you get to level 12 go back to akkanon to get your spells. Gte these ones: elemental earth, burnout, bind affinity, cancel magic, and maybe collum of fire. Again just ask higher level players for a little money if you REALLY need it, to them a few plat is nothing. Once you have your spells i suggest the minotaur caves. Fight any minotaurs that con blue, white, or yellow. be sure to keep your pet buffed with burnout and flame shielding while fighting. When done fighting cast cancel magic on your pet. Why? Becuase burnout makes your pet regain hp slower.  When you have full mana and your pet almost or totally full in hp go fight another minotaur(and keep pet buffed with burnout and flame shield, they make a good difference). If you feel like you need to group then just ask someone that is within 2 levels of you. The minotaurs someontimes gang up on you so you might need more help. Also on a sidenote you will need to buy lapis lazil to summon your pet, it no longer takes malachite. Well I am now level 13 by fight minotaurs, and that is still what I am doing to get exp. I hope your journeys are great, have fun!
